2. The Step Diagram Router (Workflow Engine)
This layer acts as a "traffic controller," deciding how to process a request based on the user's custom details. 
Request Analyzer: A specialized component that examines incoming prompts against the user profile (e.g., income level, spending 
habits) to determine the routing path.
Intent-Based Router: You can use a smaller, faster model (like Qwen 1.75B) specifically trained to categorize user intents (e.g., 
"Analyze monthly rent" vs. "Project yearly savings") and route them to the appropriate budget-handling logic.
Router Implementation:
Deterministic Routing: Simple rules (e.g., "if query length < 50 words, use fast model").
Dynamic Routing: Uses an LLM classifier or embeddings to send inputs to the most suitable model or function based on complexity. 
