3. Key Deployment Instances & Components
To deploy this as a standalone project, your architecture should include:
User Profile Database: A relational database (e.g., PostgreSQL) to store the structured "custom user details" that feed into the router.
LLM Gateway: A central middleware layer that manages authentication, rate limiting, and fallback logic if a specific model or service is unavailable.
Execution Layer (Tools): Instead of the LLM doing all the math, provide the brain with tools (Python scripts or APIs) for actual
budget calculations. The LLM acts as the orchestrator that decides which tool to call.
Containerization: Use Docker to bundle your brain, router, and database for consistent deployment across different environments.

